<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
Baelish,<P>I think they are responding to the influx of new RPGs that have PvP as a central theme, not out of any overriding interest in fixing PvP in and of itself.  If AO, Shadowbane, and DAOC were not coming out this year, I think Verant/Sony would have a 'business as usual' attitude about the PvP servers they have shown all along.  Now 'The Vision' (tm) is changing to encompass PvP - I can't understand why it wasn't addressed before if they knew it was broken...which only leads back to my first sentence - the needs of the business dictated what would be done and when.  <P>Another aspect of this that is interesting is that they have taken the GMs out of the 'police pvp' arena.  That was brilliant from a fiscal standpoint.  I would wager that 90% of the customer service buget for PvP servers was spent on PvP. PvP has never been coded right in the first place (to make these issues unambiguous to begin with) and what 'rules' there were were arbitrarily administered by GMs who had a 'book' of rules that the players were not allowed to see!  If they had any altruistic motives this sad state of affairs would not have gone on as long as it did - tearing up the fabric of the server population to such an extent that a large portion of the populations jumped at the chance for a fresh start (myself included).<P>All of that being said, I do applaud thier actions from a practical standpoint:  they are starting to get a better grasp of what a PvP server should look like and how it should function - and all of us will reap the reward when this goes live (and my $10 will continue to flow into Sony's bank account).  <P>As you can probably tell, I prefer the 'right thing' over greedy considerations.  I feel if a company does the 'right thing' the money will just naturally follow.  Unfortunately once most companies get past their heady startup days and grow into lumbering giants (ne Sony) they lose the desire to take risk (ironically enough when they are at a point when they can take more risks without going out of business due to a 'learning experience').<P>My thumb is up  on this one, but I am keeping my eyes open because Sony and Verant do not have my best interests at heart.  <IMG SRC="cool.gif" border="0"><P>--------------------<P>Let slip the dogs of war!
</FONT>
