I feel like every time Sony/Verant takes a step forward with PvP, they take three steps back. Once again, this holds true. Hardcoding the teams is something that is not only wanted, but is necessary to stop the exploiting of the game that has been done for FAR too long by crossteaming guilds. But to allow bind-rushing, corpse-camping and exp killing is just flat-out STUPID. Verant let loose with both barrels - straight into their feet on this one. They might think they're doing right, but in all likelihood, with no GM interference with regard to PvP issues, the annoying lamers who love nothing more than corpse-camping and bind-rushing will be happy, while the vast majority of players will not...and I think that a goodly number of those players will leave EQ for good, myself likely numbered in that group. Nice going, Verant. You did it again.
