All I can say is, THANK TUNARE I LEFT PvP. I made the mistake of starting EverQuest on a PvP server. If I hadn't voluntarily quit my 50 cleric (lot of work and friends to leave behind) this would be the end of my EQ career. <P>Don't get me wrong. I really *like* a *few* of the changes. The coding to remove crossteaming, in particular, as well as the (proposed) removal of common. As a DE cleric, I never crossteamed or grouped with crossteamers. Hell, being stubborn I dispelled clarity 2 from a crossteamer 11 times in a row (No, I wasn't doing anything that I needed it for, was just being an ass) ;P<P>But the bind camping, corpse camping, training, losing experience for PvP deaths, being able to attack ANYONE.. c'mon Verant. That's what you were making SV for. No one that created a character on VZ or TZ signed up for this kind of thing, and while some may like it, I have the *very* strong feeling that the majority feel as I do. And while I, personally, can't stand crossteaming, it should be pointed out that on Vallon Zek (when I quit), approximately 85-90% of players level 50 and above were in crossteaming guilds. That's a *LOT* of players, Verant. I would have suggested a more gradual approach.<P>And what's with the push with allowing people to legally bind camp you and (theoretically) cause you to lose 10 levels? I mean, you think that's ANYONES idea of fun? Or are you just trying to get EverQuest PvP a worse reputation then Ultima's? heh.<P>Add a big /boggle for me.<P>--------------------<P>I'm not a vegetarian because I like animals, I'm a vegetarian because I hate plants.<BR>      - - - -<BR>If at first you don't succeed, skydiving is not for you.
