<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
I sent the following e-mail to Verant a few minutes ago. I'm not sure if it was long enough to fit into the last post as an edit, so here it is, as I sent it:<P> <BLOCKQUOTE><font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial">quote:</font><HR><BR>I don't want to argue with Verant Interactive's choice to modify the PvP servers in such a way as they see fit. I do, however, have serious concerns about the complete destruction of the social structure of two established servers and the abandonment of Customer Service responsibility on another.<P>I believe I speak for quite a few stunned EQ players on these servers when I ask Verant for an immediate and unconditional /movelog from any and all of the Zek servers to ANY server of the player's choosing. Or, failing that, the addition of several new servers, INCLUDING one blue server, and an unconditional /movelog between any of those servers.<P>In other words, you would have the following options available if you play on Rallos, Tallon, or Vallon Zek:<P>1) Rallos Zek (General PvP, no PnP)<BR>2) Tallon Zek (Good vs. Evil, if I recall right, hardcoded, no PnP)<BR>3) Vallon Zek (Teams, hardcoded, no PnP)<BR>4) Sullon Zek (Diety Teams, hardcoded, no PnP)<BR>5) New "Guildwar" Server (possibly?)<BR>6) New/Old "Blue" Server (non-PvP)<P>All transfers would be WITH items, experience, etc.<P>This is the only fair and justified option given that the majority of players had NO intention of this being the server they would play on. I know this was NOT my intent in making several Tallon Zek characters and several Rallos Zek characters. Had this change been announced as a "pending" thing from the start, or from when I started my character, your actions would be utterly understandable and unarguable. As it stands, changing established servers is unfair *unless* a choice is offered to those of us who wish to leave a server whose policies we did NOT "agree" to when creating our characters nor even knew were POSSIBLE or PLANNED (sorry for the highlighting in caps).<P>Whatever you do, do not take this hinted-at "fee for transfer" policy and force us to comply with it if we wish to move. Particularly if we would wind up on a new server "naked." This is unfair, and moreover, would border on theft (and it is certainly unethical) of otherwise loyal players.<P>So to conclude - please give us a VERY liberal /movelog option. I would take it, as, I expect, would a fair proportion of the Zek server populations.<BR><HR></BLOCKQUOTE><P>I hope Verant is listening.<P>--------------------<P>Mintzy Fresch,<BR>Rallos Zek
