Just some comments on things I've seen:<P>Lady D is a huge fan of PVP.  I don't think the changes are meant to "break the Zeks."  I do not think they are the right changes and I'm working on a draft commentary right now.  However, on RZ specifically, training/bind point camping/intentional exp lossing occurs on a daily basis and goes unpunished.  Folks like myself that play by the rules have no recourse when people do this to us.  Now we have legal ability to fight back against the griefers -- the problem is I'm not sure that it fixes anything.<P>LD said no movelog.  I hadn't heard of the charge to move players idea until today or I sure as heck would have asked.<P>One thing that I didn't include in my submission: the /guildwar code for blue servers may be completely redone if any of you bluebies care. =)<P>I took pretty extensive notes so if anyone has any questions that I can answer let me know. One of the things that was dropped from my news submission is the warning not to assume anything until the changes are announced.  Don't start training folks as you'll end up banned until the pnp is lifted.  It may end up not lifted but that's what was communicated.<P>Cheers,<P>  Rafinne L`Ongbone<BR>  Warlock<BR>  Rallos Zek
