<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
Well, I think 1/2 of you will bite my ear off, but here'goes....<P>First of all I like the idea of no cross teaming and disbanding guilds.  Yes, it may break up friends and break ties...but it will also eliminate things like the immune clerics and other ways to beat the system.<P>Second, the ability to attack any person at any level...This makes sense...i dont see how it would make be realistic for someone to be invulnerable if they were a few levels higher or lower, it adds more to the "roleplay" effect.<P>About the losing of experience....someone would not be able to lower you all the way down to level 1 unless they themselves deleveled...and this would be of no advantage to them, so there would be no point in doing it.  Also, if someone becomes a super jerk about bind camping and such, some higher level person (or same level if 60) will most likely be in the vicinity to help out.<P>As for the no common language, I love it.  Different races dont know how to speak other languages fluently in the real world, and there is no common language in the real world...why on Norrath should it be different?<P>40 hours for a quest that allows you to change teams, I think this is a pretty good idea. Some may complain that it takes too long, etc, I say just be happy that they give the chance ;-)<P>I think thats all I have to post about for now.  (Ducks the oncoming flames)<BR>  <IMG SRC="smile.gif" border="0">
</FONT>
